{"word":"πρόσπολος","slug":"πρόσπολος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πρόσπολος</b></el> <el>(πρός-πολος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πολέω'><el>πολέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a servant</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <i>a ministering priest</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>πρ. φόνου</el> <i>minister</i> of death, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> <i>a handmaid</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}